      "creatureType": "",
      "blurb": "Chained spirit of Scarwall",
      "publicNotes": "<h3>Conversion notes (this module)</h3><p><strong>Role:</strong> Scarwall's castellan, who died on Serithtial's edge buying Kazavon time to retreat — now the <strong>chained spirit</strong> at the heart of the curse, enthroned beside his master's empty chair in the Great Hall (C14). Every bound soul in the walls is his to spend; he commands vast necromancy but cannot directly act elsewhere in the castle, and he <em>fears for his anchors</em>. <strong>Destroying him (after the four anchors) frees every trapped soul, lifts the curse — and wakes <em>Serithtial</em>.</strong></p>",
      "privateNotes": ""
    },
